article.headline: SE Missouri 33, Austin Peay 30
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. -- Timmy Holloman scored on a 1-yard touchdown to lift Southeast Missouri to a 33-30 win over Austin Peay on Saturday. Austin Peay (2-8, 2-5 Ohio Valley Conference) led 30-26 when it punted with 4:11 left in the fourth quarter. The Redhawks (4-8, 2-6) used the rest of the time as Holloman was denied at the goal line three times before scoring the game-winning touchdown on fourth down. Matt Scheible connected with Chante Ahamefule on a 27-yard touchdown pass to give Southeast Missouri a 30-26 lead in the fourth quarter. The extra point was missed. Scheible completed 12 of 14 passes for 195 yards and three touchdowns. Walter Peoples had three catches -- two for scores -- for 81 yards. The Governors evened the score on a Trent Caffee 1-yard scramble and took a lead after blocked punt returned for a touchdown followed by a 41-yard field goal by Issac Ziolkowski. Austin Peay held that lead, matching the Redhawks score-for-score, until the game's final seconds. Caffee threw for 118 yards and a touchdown, as well as rushing for a score. Ryan White carried the ball 19 times for 80 yards, while Jeff Lyle caught the Govs only touchdown pass. Ziolkowski, returning from an injury, kicked a season-high three field goals. It was the last game of the season for both teams.
